{"type":"message","id":"4b1bec92","parentId":"fdc4cc7b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T04:05:09.669Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to handle this cron reminder internally. Let me check for new messages to sync to Second Brain.\n\nI need to:\n1. Check the last sync timestamp\n2. Look for any new memory files since the last sync\n3. Process and sync them to the Second Brain (Obsidian vault)\n4. Update the sync timestamp\n\nLet me start by reading the necessary files.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_ibOzdwXE84xjJMBSe2An1Ipm","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/memory/second-brain/last-sync.timestamp"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_wNC5eJuM7TeFT9rm2DCFUjjG","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-03.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_QFEhd4gIgXbBf0toayYcC46W","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-02.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":20479,"output":179,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21938,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775189099522}}
{"type":"message","id":"a06a50c0","parentId":"4b1bec92","timestamp":"2026-04-03T04:05:09.699Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_ibOzdwXE84xjJMBSe2An1Ipm","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-03T03:57:00Z\",\n  \"entries_synced\": 0,\n  \"sync_source\": \"cron-pipeline\",\n  \"last_sync_from\": null,\n  \"status\": \"no-new-content\",\n  \"checked_files\": [\"2026-04-03.md\"]\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775189109697}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c9577eb","parentId":"a06a50c0","timestamp":"2026-04-03T04:05:09.704Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_wNC5eJuM7TeFT9rm2DCFUjjG","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory Flush - 2026-04-03\n\n## Critical Bug Discovery: `edit` Tool Parameter Issue\n\n### Problem Identified\nThe `edit` tool has a **fundamental bug** in tool-call generation. The `new_string` (or `newText`) parameter cannot be correctly passed to the gateway.\n\n**Error Pattern:**\n```\nMissing required parameter: newText (newText or new_string). Supply correct parameters before retrying.\n```\n\n### Evidence from Testing\n- Gateway logs confirm the parameter never arrives: `[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText...`\n- Tested with both `new_string` and `newText` parameter names - neither works\n- The parameter validation happens at the gateway level (thread-bindings-SYAnWHuW.js)\n- Schema shows: `{ keys: [\"newText\", \"new_string\"], label: \"newText (newText or new_string)\", allowEmpty: true }`\n\n### Workaround Solution\n**Use `read` + `write` instead of `edit`** for file modifications:\n\n1. `read` the file content\n2. `write` the modified content back\n\nExample:\n```\nread file.txt          # Get current content\nwrite file.txt \"new\"   # Write modified content\n```\n\n### Impact\n- All file edits must use the read+write pattern\n- Cannot use precise `edit` for surgical changes\n- More verbose but functional workaround exists\n\n### Next Steps\n- Consider creating a skill that wraps read+write as an `edit` replacement\n- Document this limitation in TOOLS.md\n- Monitor for gateway updates that might fix this\n\n---\n*Flush time: 2026-04-03 02:38 CET*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775189109699}}
{"type":"message","id":"20f47cf4","parentId":"9c9577eb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T04:05:09.709Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_QFEhd4gIgXbBf0toayYcC46W","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Log - 2026-04-02\n\n## Major Accomplishments\n\n### 1. Fixed Critical Compilation Errors\n- Resolved E0502 borrow checker errors in `mcp_stdio.rs` by using standalone functions\n- Fixed zyklische Abhängigkeit (circular dependency) between memory-compaction and ecc-runtime\n- Corrected string concatenation in format!() macros (using \\ continuation instead of +)\n- Added missing exports (SimpleSummarizer, MessageSummary) to lib.rs\n\n### 2. All 4 Core Components Implemented ✅\n| Component | Location | Tests | Status |\n|-----------|----------|-------|--------|\n| SSE Streaming | `skills/secure-api-client/src/streaming.rs` | 8 passed | ✅ Complete |\n| Conversation Runtime | `crates/ecc-runtime/src/lib.rs` | 9 passed | ✅ Complete |\n| Permission Framework | `skills/security-review/src/permissions.rs` | 14 passed | ✅ Complete |\n| Session Compaction | `crates/memory-compaction/src/compactor.rs` | 22 passed | ✅ Complete |\n\n**Total: 60/60 tests passing across all crates**\n\n### 3. Web Fetch Tool Added\n- Implemented `WebFetchTool` and `UrlCheckTool` in `tool-registry/src/tools/web_fetch.rs`\n- Features: HTTP GET/POST, retry logic, content truncation, URL validation\n- Blocks internal IPs (localhost, 192.168.x, etc.) for security\n- All 11 tool-registry tests passing\n\n### 4. Architecture Decision Record Created\n- **ADR-001**: Documented decision NOT to implement CLAW.md Discovery\n- Reason: Single-project setup, SOUL.md + MEMORY.md sufficient\n- File: `docs/ADR-001-no-claw-discovery.md`\n\n### 5. MCP Tool Adapter Started\n- Created `crates/ecc-runtime/src/mcp_integration.rs`\n- Implements `ToolExecutor` trait for MCP servers\n- Tool naming format: `mcp.{server_name}.{tool_name}`\n- Currently has Send/Sync compilation issues with Mutex - needs fix\n\n## Workspace Status\n\n### Build Status\n```\n✅ memory-compaction: 22 tests passing\n✅ ecc-runtime: 9 tests passing  \n✅ security-review: 14 tests passing\n✅ secure-api-client: 8 tests passing\n✅ tool-registry: 7 tests passing\n```\n\n### Release Build\n- All crates compile in release mode\n- Only minor warnings (dead_code for planned features)\n\n## Files Modified Today\n- `crates/memory-compaction/src/compactor.rs` - Fixed warnings\n- `crates/memory-compaction/src/obsidian_sync.rs` - Fixed string concat\n- `crates/memory-compaction/src/sync_pipeline.rs` - Fixed type mismatches\n- `crates/memory-compaction/src/lib.rs` - Added exports\n- `crates/memory-compaction/src/classifier.rs` - Fixed Default trait\n- `crates/memory-compaction/tests/compaction_tests.rs` - Fixed imports\n- `crates/ecc-runtime/src/mcp_stdio.rs` - Fixed borrow checker\n- `crates/ecc-runtime/src/memory_bridge.rs` - Removed unused imports\n- `crates/ecc-runtime/src/lib.rs` - Added MCP integration module\n- `skills/security-review/src/risk_analyzer.rs` - Added value() method\n- `skills/security-review/src/lib.rs` - Updated exports\n- `skills/security-review/src/permissions.rs` - Minor fixes\n- `skills/security-review/tests/permissions_tests.rs` - Fixed imports\n- `skills/secure-api-client/src/streaming.rs` - Already complete\n- `skills/tool-registry/src/tools/web_fetch.rs` - NEW\n- `skills/tool-registry/src/tools/mod.rs` - Updated exports\n- `skills/tool-registry/Cargo.toml` - Added reqwest dependency\n- `docs/ADR-001-no-claw-discovery.md` - NEW\n- `FUTURE_FEATURES.md` - NEW (vorgemerkte Features)\n- `IMPLEMENTATION_ANALYSIS.md` - NEW (detaillierte Analyse)\n\n## Key Learnings\n\n### Rust Patterns\n1. **Borrow Checker**: Use standalone functions instead of &self methods when both mutable and immutable borrows needed\n2. **String Concatenation**: Use `\\` line continuation in format!() instead of `+` operator\n3. **Trait Exports**: Must export both Struct AND Trait for methods to be usable\n4. **Mutex in Async**: Use `tokio::sync::Mutex` instead of `std::sync::Mutex` for Send compatibility\n\n### PowerShell Best Practices\n- Use `${var}` syntax for variable interpolation with special chars\n- Use `takeown` before `icacls` on Windows\n- ASCII-only output (no emojis) for German Windows compatibility\n\n## Open Tasks\n\n### High Priority\n1. Fix MCP Tool Adapter Send/Sync issues (use tokio::sync::Mutex)\n2. Complete MCP integration testing\n\n### Medium Priority (Documented in FUTURE_FEATURES.md)\n1. Process Isolation (Docker) for Autoresearch\n2. LLM-based Compaction (currently using SimpleSummarizer)\n3. Extended Security validation\n\n### Low Priority / Won't Implement\n1. CLAW.md Discovery (documented decision against it)\n2. Plugin System\n3. CLI Binary (not needed for OpenClaw Gateway)\n\n## Next Steps (Recommended)\n1. Fix MCP Tool Adapter Mutex issue\n2. Run full workspace test suite\n3. Create integration test for MCP + Runtime\n4. Document usage examples\n\n---\n*Session ended: 2026-04-02 22:02 CET*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775189109706}}
